korean:
  title: 고의
  author: 최사제
  language: kor
  text: |-
    복희씨와 헌원씨는 너무 바삐 갔네
    천지는 어이하여 그리 일찍 개벽했노
    머리 풀어헤치고 맑은 바람에 누우니
    새 한 마리 저 하늘 푸른 속으로 파묻혀 가네
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0220_010_0060&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: Ancient Sentiment
  author: Choi Sa-je
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Fuxi and Huangdi rushed through their days in such haste—
    Why did heaven and earth part so early?
    Hair loosened, I lie in the pure wind,
    A lone bird vanishes into the depths of blue sky.
  footnotes:
    - Fuxi and Huangdi (Huang Di) are legendary Chinese sage-kings, here representing the distant past and the rapid passage of time
    - The poet contrasts the restless bustle of the ancients with the speaker's moment of repose in nature, suggesting a philosophical meditation on temporality and human ambition
